description: For sale: $194,900. Welcome to this completely remodeled 2 bedroom, 1 bathroom home located in a great neighborhood! As you walk into the home you will love the front porch, open floor plan, and updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances! This home features 2 bedrooms on the main level, fresh paint throughout, new flooring, new windows, and newer siding! There is a full lower level that is unfinished and great for storage! A truly convenient and prime location close to parks, lakes, shopping, schools, dining and more!

For sale: $350,000. Look no further than this updated Cape Cod style home in an amazing location, just steps to Minnehaha Creek and the Light Rail. Convenience is right outside your doorstep with countless neighborhood amenities including Minnehaha Regional Park, Lake Nokomis and Hiawatha, Oxendale's Market, Town Hall Lanes, Sea Salt Eatery, breweries and more. Less than 10 minutes to the airport and a direct route downtown via the Blue Line. Property amenities do not disappoint either! Beautifully updated while maintaining the home's charm. 2012 water heater, 2006 furnace and newer appliances including brand new fridge. Light and bright upper level master suite with private 3/4 bath, renovated kitchen, plus finished lower level with spacious family room and great storage. Main floor den can easily be converted back to legal third bedroom based upon buyer's needs. Backyard patio, quiet block, and great curb appeal. Meticulously maintained property in an unmatched location.

description: For sale: $219,000. Charming Standish Neighborhood house within walking distance of light rail and shops, coffee shops and restaurants. The seller has gone to great expense to rescue this house. You will find everything in working order and lots of warmth and charm.  It is small but it is complete and the outdoor areas  are ready for gardening, playing and lounging in front of the fire pit. All appliances are included. This is a very manageable house for a single or small group. The lower level bedroom has egress and a very large closet.  The garage has room for two cars and your other equipment. The seller is meticulous and you will find the house sparkling clean and very organized. The kitchen has recently been redone and has lots of light and space. An extra pantry can hold a lot of goods. The utility costs are:  gas $38 per month;electricity $39 per month and water/trash/sewer $62 per month.  This is a great price for this house at a very convenient location.

description:
For sale: $360,000. Charming home in the heart of Seward with abundant, spectacular woodwork and updated kitchen awaits new owners.  You will love the open stair case, box beam ceilings, built-in bookshelves and buffet.  Don't miss the leaded and stained glass windows!   The kitchen, which has plenty of counter space, has a sweet dine-in area and pantry area adjacent to it. Other bonus spaces include  a sun room large enough for a grand piano,  an office nook on the second floor, an upper level deck, and in the basement there is a partially finished bonus room in addition to the family room both of which have concrete floors. 
The newer two-car garage is attached to an older garage which is used for things other than parking cars.  
This house is in a sweet spot near The Birchwood and the Mississippi River.

description: For sale: $259,900. There is character and charm found throughout this 1.5 story home! There are beautiful engravings in the woodwork, the hardwood floors beam, and the stained-glass window shines in the afternoon light. The large kitchen has exposed brick, stainless steel appliances, a lovely tile backsplash, and loads of cabinet and counter space. There are lots of opportunities to create a home office whether it's on the porch, the upstairs loft, or one of the extra bedrooms. The backyard is a wonderful at-home sanctuary! The patio under the Pergola can be a lounging place to unwind after a long day. The surrounding area has lakes to enjoy, shops and restaurants to walk to, and easy access to the light rail. There's lots of storage and wonderful features here inside and out. Come and see all this home offers!

The 3/4 bath has a fiberglass shower stall again no maintenance of tile and grout and no leaks. The vanity has 3 drawers and a one piece top and a matching light bar medicine mirrored cabinet. There is storage cabinet above the toilet with an accompanied storage tower with 5 drawers.

description: For sale: $699,900. This beautiful 1928 Tudor combines charming period details with comfortable contemporary updates. Light fills the solarium, and the spacious living room with marble inset fireplace. The conservatory views a private fenced back garden with patio and lush low maintenance landscaping. The architecturally designed kitchen renovation blends fine woodwork with modern conveniences. Four corner bedrooms include large, sunny windows and a view of the river gorge. Lower level features family room with gas fireplace and tiled warm floor, spacious exercise area, and small bedroom/office and bathroom with shower. Oversized two car garage offers space for workshop, bikes, and storage. It's a dream lifestyle for dog lovers, cyclists and runners, with paved bike-paths, greenway access, and river trails starting just outside your door. Together with neighborhood cafes, coop and yoga, quick routes to the university, downtown, and the airport, the best of urban life meets outdoor parkway fun-right here!

description: Recently sold: $435,000. Spacious, spotless home in high-demand Ericsson neighborhood - hard to find 4 bedrooms and 2 bathrooms above ground! Light and bright main floor features generous living room with gas fireplace, hardwood floors, 2 bedrooms, 3/4 bath with heated floor, plus an updated kitchen with bay window, quartz counters, tile back splash, stainless appliances, and quartz-topped movable island. Upper level lives like a 2-story, with 2 more bedrooms, full bath with heated floor, plus a sunny loft area and large walk-in closet. Expansive lower level family room with gas fireplace, included 4K projector and screen, and separate exercise room. Fenced backyard with terrific large deck, plus a 2 car garage. Smart home with Alexa-controlled lights, heat, fans, digital locks. Ideal location with Minnehaha Creek at the end of the block, with Lake Nokomis, Lake Hiawatha, Minnehaha Falls, the Blue Line light rail station, plus local shops and restaurants all within walking distance. A terrific opportunity!

description: Recently sold: $315,000. Walking into this updated home makes it a tough decision whether you want to enjoy a night in or head back out to enjoy all that Longfellow has to offer. Just steps away is The Blue Door, the Riverview Theater, Lake Street dining & shopping, hiking/biking along the Mississippi, etc. Waiting to welcome you back home is the enchanting front porch. This bright, remodeled kitchen with custom cabinetry is especially noteworthy. When you head upstairs-be sure check out the bath vanity & walk-in closet in the spacious master suite. Never haul a laundry basket downstairs again! Laundry on the upper floor with all the bedrooms makes light work & could almost be considered a luxurious task thanks to the heated floor warming your toes. The interior has updated windows & a floor plan that allows for a small carbon footprint & low maintenance costs. Travel to/from home is easy by bus, car, bike, train or on foot. And did we mention Turtle Bread is right around the corner? You will love living here!

Recently sold: $290,000. Fully renovated home hitting the market. Everything has been redone top to bottom inside and out. For further details call, text or email. Also check out our FB page Remodeling The Twin Cities to see what we've done in the past.

description: Recently sold: $181,500. Rare opportunity for a move-in ready charming stucco bungalow with central AC, gleaming hardwood floors, plenty of natural light throughout, a nice yard, updated mechanicals and electrical, a spacious 16 x 12 bedroom and much more! Tiled bathroom next to convenient linen closet. Updated kitchen overlooks the sunny backyard with bunny-proof garden area. Unfinished basement has plenty of storage, a large cedar closet, shelves under the stairs for convenient storage and expansion potential with good ceiling height and plenty of additional square footage. description: Recently sold: $480,000. Multiple offers received! This modest 1920's foursquare near Minnehaha Falls was your typical boxy stuccoed two story with practical space that did not call too much attention to itself.  At least, not until HGTV got a hold of it!  The design was a collaboration between P/K Architecture, design build manager Dan Faires, & Joshua Ortmeier from Reuter Walton Const.  In back, they built a 500 sq/foot addition to accomodate a new living room and mudroom on the 1st floor, plus a master suite on the second.  In the kitchen, a wall of cabinets conceals the fridge & pantry and includes a clever nook for a big window & professional style range.  Upstairs features two bedrooms a full bath plus the new master suite w/bathroom that boasts luxurious touches.  All these interior designs were led by designer Patrick Flynn.  The clean black & white color scheme, light wood floors, natural materials, variety of textiles, make this "Scandinavian farmhouse" embrace a comfortable & cozy lifestyle.

description: Recently sold: $276,000. Really cute Bungalow beautifully maintained with original features revered by many! Many period style light fixtures, glass/brass door hardware, windows, wood flooring and gorgeous built ins w/beveled glass including the buffet, book cases, linen cabinet, medicine cabinet & a cozy breakfast nook. Wall of kitchen cabinetry w/original hardware. Travertine & Slate tile in updated bath. Vented glass block windows in bathrooms and basement. Yearly professional maintenance & updating has been key to preserving mechanicals. Beautiful brick fireplace flanked by original built in book cases with glass doors. Roof is newer w/fresh paint on gutters, exterior & garage. Newer paver patio. Awesome expansion area with walk up stairs ready for your personal finishing. Would make a wonderful art or music studio, play room or extra bedroom. Those with appreciation for quality craftsmanship & the beauty of preserving, this is your home. Walk to Minnehaha Park, Cub foods, light rail and more.

description: Recently sold: $359,000. Location location location - close to the river pathways for biking and walking. Come prepared to put your ideas to work and build equity in this mechanically sound home. New Roof just 1 month old, New PECS Water Supply line, 12 year old furnace, Central Air 2 years old. Charm of hardwood floors throughout main level, built in buffet in dining room, and efficient kitchen. Two main floor bedrooms and a 3/4 bath round out this level. The upper level has three bedrooms with ample closet space, and ability fo refinish hardwood floors, a bathroom with claw foot tub and skylight above.  Relax on second level porch, or on the front porch for having a cup of coffee. Garage is insulated, heated and there's an extra off-street parking space. Trim and fascia just painted. Low maintenance yard - Basement has potential to finish.

Recently sold: $356,000. Hurry - will go fast! Rare opportunity to invest in a side-by-side bungalow duplex one block from Minnehaha Parkway and Minnehaha Falls! Loads of equity for an owner occupant or investor in this charming 1947-built double bungalow with original hardwood floors and crown molding! Both sides have identical floor plans with spacious light-filled living rooms, eat-in kitchens, two bedrooms and a full bath on the main level. Each side has a full unfinished basement for additional living space potential or storage. 4720 side also has a 3/4 bath in the basement. There is a shared front deck with a ramp, lovely landscaping and a shared driveway with a two-car detached garage with additional space for off-street parking. You will love the location - close to city bus and light rail with easy access to Minneapolis or St.Paul. Endless opportunity for enjoyment, with Minnehaha Park only steps away!

description:
Recently sold: $422,000. Welcome to the 1925 craftsman bungalow duplex hailing from the Longfellow neighborhood of Minneapolis! Outfitted with all of the original detailing you expect from a duplex of this era: original hardwoods throughout, formal built-in in dining room, original floor to ceiling shaker cabinets in kitchen, hex tile floor in bath, piano windows and archways. Unit includes free laundry in basement and garage parking spot as well as a fully fenced in backyard! Brand-new German Haier refrigerator and commercial style GE range just ordered to bring more modern functionality to the kitchen. Walkability score is 10/10! Nestled right in between the Mississippi River and Minnehaha Ave. You have access to everything in the surrounding area: Peace Coffee, Parkway Pizza, Trylon movie theater, Riverview movie theater, Riverview Wine Bar, Blue Door Pub, Turtle Bread, Hi Lo Diner, Minnehaha Falls & Sea Salt Eatery! Very easy access to both Downtown Minneapolis & Downtown Saint Paul as well as quick access to western suburbs. Pets allowed on a case-by-case basis.

Owner pays: water, sewer, trash, recycling. Tenant pays for: electric, gas, internet.
